----------------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 2: Add L2 preload block BEFORE the auto-restart section (line ~40)
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Insert the following block after the "Session cleanup" fi block and BEFORE
the "# --- Auto-restart with exponential backoff ---" comment:

    # --- L2 on-demand block preload ---
    # Generates /tmp/anya-l2-context.md with matched block contents.
    # Pass a context hint as $1 (first arg to start.sh) to enable matching.
    # CLAUDE.md startup section tells Anya to read this file if it exists.
    INITIAL_QUERY="${1:-}"
    if [[ -n "$INITIAL_QUERY" ]] && [[ -f "$L2_LOADER" ]]; then
      python3 - <<'PYEOF'
    import sys, os
    sys.path.insert(0, os.path.expanduser('~/.claude-bots/shared/lib'))
    from l2_loader import L2Loader, log_session
    from pathlib import Path

    blocks_dir = os.path.expanduser('~/.claude-bots/bots/anya/blocks')
    context_file = '/tmp/anya-l2-context.md'
    stats_path = os.path.expanduser('~/.claude-bots/state/anya/l2_stats.json')
    initial_query = os.environ.get('_L2_INITIAL_QUERY', '')

    loader = L2Loader(blocks_dir)
    matched = loader.match(initial_query)

    if matched:
        lines = [f'<!-- L2 context: {len(matched)} block(s) matched at startup -->\n']
        for path in matched:
            lines.append(f'\n<!-- === {Path(path).name} === -->\n')
            lines.append(Path(path).read_text(encoding='utf-8'))
        with open(context_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:
            f.write('\n'.join(lines))
        print(f'[L2] Preloaded {len(matched)} block(s) -> {context_file}')
        log_session(initial_query, matched, stats_path=stats_path)
    else:
        if os.path.exists(context_file):
            os.remove(context_file)
        print('[L2] No blocks matched.')
    PYEOF
      export _L2_INITIAL_QUERY="$INITIAL_QUERY"
    elif [[ -f "$L2_CONTEXT_FILE" ]]; then
      rm -f "$L2_CONTEXT_FILE"
    fi

NOTE: The heredoc approach avoids shell variable quoting issues in the query.
Set _L2_INITIAL_QUERY env var before calling the python block (shown above).

